{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648001","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648001"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:48:45+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:48:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18270"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18270","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18270"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10984"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79315"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10984","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10984"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18270"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64637"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25518"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25522"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27145"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79315","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79315"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is true regarding the positioning of the patella?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The apex of the patella is attached to the fibula via the patellar ligament","The base of the patella is attached to the tibial tuberosity","The patella is located within the hamstring tendon","The patella sits anteriorly to the femoral condyles","The patella sits anteriorly to the femoral epicondyles"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe patella is a sesamoid bone located within the quadriceps tendon, and it sits \u003Cstrong\u003Eanteriorly to the femoral condyles\u003C/strong\u003E. This positioning allows it to function as a fulcrum, increasing the leverage of the quadriceps muscle during knee extension.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eapex of the patella\u003C/strong\u003E is attached to the tibial tuberosity via the patellar ligament, not the fibula. This attachment is crucial for the transmission of forces from the quadriceps muscle to the tibia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe patella does not sit anteriorly to the \u003Cstrong\u003Efemoral epicondyles\u003C/strong\u003E, as these are located more laterally and posteriorly relative to the patella.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe patella is not located within the \u003Cstrong\u003Ehamstring tendon\u003C/strong\u003E; it is within the quadriceps tendon.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebase of the patella\u003C/strong\u003E is the superior part of the bone and is not directly attached to the tibial tuberosity; it is the apex that is connected via the patellar ligament.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The patella is a sesamoid bone located within the quadriceps tendon.","The patella sits anteriorly to the femoral condyles, not the epicondyles.","The patellar ligament attaches the apex of the patella to the tibial tuberosity, not the fibula."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537024/","Raftery A. General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006 Jul;88(4):425. doi: 10.1308/003588406X114802d. PMCID: PMC1964629","Chaudhry SR, Nahian A, Chaudhry K. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis, Pelvis. [Updated 2023 Jul 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482258/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64637"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18270"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64637","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64637"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-14T09:12:57+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-14T09:13:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10984"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79315"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4931","links":{"self":"ht